  "description": "Is A Product Feature that defines how a beneficiary, policyholder, or authorized party initiates a claim for benefits under a funeral policy upon the occurrence of a covered event (e.g., death of the insured).\r\n\r\nComment:\r\nIt specifies the eligible claimant roles, required documentation (e.g., death certificate, identification, policy reference), initiation channels (e.g., branch, digital, agent), validation rules, submission timelines, and the conditions under which the claim is accepted, rejected, or escalated for assessment and payout processing.",
